        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 700 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Herrin, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Herrin, Carterville, Johnston City, Crainville, Energy,
Pittsburg, Whiteash, and Spillertown.

This includes Interstate 57 in Illinois between Mile Markers 55 and
61.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. This type of funnel cloud is harmless, but on rare occasions
they can briefly touch down, producing wind gusts over 50 mph. If a
funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your sighting to the
National Weather Service.</instruction>
